  The epic for mages is good, i will grant them that.  It is in line with their class.  Necromancers and enchanters i can't/wont comment on since i don't know anything about it.  Wizards, in my opinion, should have got a spell of some description.  An offencive spell!  <br>
  For levels upon levels, the logic of the wizard class was an over-powering offence with a pathetic defence.  So why give us a skin as an effect?  Sure the extra mana regeneration is great, but i don't think that is true to the wizard class.  In a way i suppose it does help do damage since it helps you get mana back faster, but it doesn't have the &quot;bang, you're dead&quot; mentality that is what the wizard is supposed to be about.<br>
  Well, we have had the epic weapon quest for each class.  Now i want the epic spell for each class. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Talinath.<br>
58th level Evoker. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/unastafen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nastafen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/22/01 12:46:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Wizard Epic.</span><hr size=1> Amen. I am not a wizard, but that IS a bad epic effect. Before the mage epic I would have thought this was overpowering, but how about this:<br>
Have a rightclickable effect of an UBER lure. Was every lure combined (Don't know much about wizards, but I am pretty sure they have a lure for each resistance) and did more damage than any of them. Since mages got a pet that was a combination of every pet plus added bonuses, it would only make sense to give wizards the same.<br>
Make it do 1.5 times the damage of your lures, and check against whichever resist was lowest on the creature. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uaramalg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aramalg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/22/01 3:19:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:The Wizard Epic.</span><hr size=1>   Hmm.  You have a good idea there, Nastafen.  How good would depend on the casting time and the recast time though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
